The paper deals with the construction of region graphs for Generalized Belief Propagation (GBP), which is a popular algorithm in the fields of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the identification of cycle bases on a Markov network, which is a topic related to data structures (DS) and information theory (IT). Finally, the paper discusses the improvement of the accuracy and convergence of GBP, which is a problem in the field of signal processing and communications (SI).
